	§218.27   Workers on track other than main track

This training is required for is for the following personnel:


	Signal Inspectors &amp; Testmen

The entirety of this regulation subpart can be accessed through this&nbsp;link.&nbsp;

Online Course: This training is required by the Federal Railroad Administration's (FRA) Code of Federal Regulations (CFR), Title 49. It consists of a briefing on the following section(s):&nbsp;


	§218.27   Workers on track other than main track&nbsp;
	§218.73   Warning signal display&nbsp;
	§218.75   Methods of protection for camp cars&nbsp;
	§218.77   Remotely controlled switches&nbsp;
	§218.79   Alternative methods of protection
	§218.101   Leaving rolling and on-track maintenance-of-way equipment in the clear&nbsp;
	§218.103   Hand-operated switches, including crossover switches&nbsp;
	§218.105   Additional operational requirements for hand-operated main track switches&nbsp;
	§218.107   Additional operational requirements for hand-operated crossover switches&nbsp;
	§218.109   Hand-operated fixed derails

This training is required for is for the following personnel:


	Signal Supervisors

The entirety of this regulation subpart can be accessed through this&nbsp;link.&nbsp;

Online Course: This training is required by the Federal Railroad Administration's (FRA) Code of Federal Regulations (CFR), Title 49. It consists of a briefing on the following section(s):&nbsp;


	§220.25   Instruction and operational testing of employees&nbsp;
	§220.27   Identification&nbsp;
	§220.31   Initiating a radio transmission&nbsp;
	§220.33   Receiving a radio transmission&nbsp;
	§220.35   Ending a radio transmission&nbsp;
	§220.37   Testing radio and wireless communication equipment&nbsp;
	§220.43   Radio communications consistent with federal regulations and railroad operating rules&nbsp;
	§220.45   Radio communication shall be complete&nbsp;
	§220.47   Emergency radio transmissions&nbsp;
	§220.49   Radio communication used in shoving, backing or pushing movement&nbsp;
	§220.61   Radio transmission of mandatory directives&nbsp;
	§220.303   General use of electronic devices&nbsp;
	§220.305   Use of personal electronic devices&nbsp;
	§220.307   Use of railroad-supplied electronic devices&nbsp;
	§220.309   Permitted uses; exceptions to other restrictions

This training is required for is for the following personnel:


	Signal Supervisors

The entirety of this regulation subpart can be accessed through this&nbsp;link.

Online Course: This is an instructional video for the set up and use of a TIS-4&nbsp;Track Input Simulator (Harmon, GE, Alstom).&nbsp;

This is pertinent to ONLY the TIS-4 model and NOT to any other track input simulator.&nbsp;

Please contact your Senior Systems Test Engineer if you have any questions.&nbsp;

Online Course: This is an instructional video for uploading software to an ElectroLogIXS&nbsp;(GE, Alstom).&nbsp;

This is pertinent to ONLY and ElectroLogIXS and NOT to any other microprocessor.&nbsp;

Please contact your Senior Systems Test Engineer if you have any questions.&nbsp;

Curriculum: This curriculum consists of four driver training courses. Each video will be followed by a five&nbsp;question quiz to check for understanding and confirm you watched the entire video.&nbsp;The curriculum as a whole will take about two&nbsp;hours to complete and you will have six weeks to complete it in its entirety.&nbsp;

IMPORTANT: In order to access this training, you will need to copy and paste the following policy number into the pop up window that will appear once you open the training.&nbsp;

POLICY #:&nbsp;&nbsp;LCTEMP1616631477007

Online Course: This training is required by the Federal Railroad Administration's (FRA) Code of Federal Regulations (CFR), Title 49. It consists of a briefing on the following section(s):&nbsp;


§218.27   Workers on track other than main track&nbsp;

This training is mandatory for is for the following personnel:


Signal Lineperson

The entirety of this regulation subpart can be accessed through this&nbsp;link.&nbsp;

