Online Course: 

Time cards can be troublesome - But not when you have HeavyJob Mobile. Learn how to enter hours, create schedules, and add
quantities for a seamless work day from beginning to end.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

Gain insight to how the Quote System works in HeavyBid. Take a tour through the quote system and then learn how to create quote
folders and add vendors to them.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

This course will show you how to set up Safety Alerts to notify you when important submissions come in, like Observations or incident
cases. We will also go over the Outstanding Items page so you can stay informed on what you need to focus your attention on.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

Enhance your estimating and quoting process by learning how to use the Self-Performed Work module to take accurate quotes. Easily
compare yourself against subcontract activities to determine the best cost decisions.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

In-depth exploration of HeavyBid’s Quote Summary. Learn how to take advantage of the Quote System in HeavyBid to expedite your
quoting and solicitation process.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

This implementation course will prepare users and administrators for use of the HCSS Safety software and provide an overview of the
use of the Manager and Field systems.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

Within this course you will find a detailed overview of the HCSS Safety system. We will cover all of the tasks a field safety specialist will
need to know in the mobile HCSS Safety application.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

In this series of videos, you’ll learn everything you need to know about time cards in HCSS Field. Beginning with entering hours and
ending with entering quantities, by the end of these videos you’ll be able to create and send time cards in HCSS Field mobile&nbsp;

Online Course: 

Gain a high level understanding of the HeavyJob functionality in the HCSS Field Mobile system and hear a success story from a current
HCSS Field Mobile User.&nbsp;

Online Course: 

Learn to use the Safety Application to record your inspections electronically to get quick access to reporting and history. Manage your
open inspection items through completion of follow-up to ensure the inspection loop is closed.&nbsp;
